Access Holdings Overview 
 
Access Holdings is a private investment firm which manages over $450 million of equity capital across several platforms. We proactively target essential service industries that benefit from favorable regulatory and demographic trends. We seek to create value over time through active management oversight and support of our portfolio team partners. 
 
Our investment criteria include: 
  
Position Description 
Access Holdings is seeking an outstanding candidate to work directly with the Chief Operating Officer (COO) at one of our portfolio companies. The Corporate Development and Business Intelligence Associate will be responsible for supporting the M&A activity for the enterprise, organizational analytics, ownership and effective utilization of delivery optimization tools, modeling and measuring the organization’s execution of synergies related to committed value creation with respect to service delivery, facilities, overhead, technology and processes.  
 
The role is accountable for creating, reporting, and facilitating the execution of solutions that deliver measured ROI enterprise-wide in functions of route optimization, service delivery, total labor management and product inventory management and distribution. The role supports key functions and executives in gathering information and reporting aligned to the performance scorecard and other key performance indicators as needed. While the role will report directly to the COO and will provide business intelligence support across the organization, the role will work closely with managing partners, principles, and associates at the PE firm, and should expect to receive direction from the COO, CFO and Head of M&A regularly.       
  
 
Education, Work Experience Requirements and/or Competencies:  
  
The position will be based in Baltimore, Maryland. 
 
Contact 
 
Please apply through LinkedIn or email your resume and cover letter to Recruiting@accessholdings.com. If emailing, please ensure to the Subject Line states "Corporate Development and Business Intelligence Associate"

FirstKey HomesMarietta, Georgia 
 
SUMMARY OF RESPONSIBILITIESThe Business Intelligence Manager will serve as a thought leader for conceptualizing and operationalizing business intelligence initiatives. This role will consult with business leaders to understand their line of business and provide solutions with their data and reporting needs. S/he will help departments with sourcing, aggregating, accessing and interpreting datato increase the effectiveness of decision making during a time of rapid organizational growth. Additionally, the Business Intelligence Manager will lead a small team of direct reports, resolve escalated issues and lead process improvement projects.  
ESSENTIAL DUTIES● Serve as a primary thought leader for all business intelligence initiatives. Assist in conceptualizing and definingstrategies as well as leading and coordinating efforts to operationalize concepts throughout the business.● Assess the current state of reporting, analytics and business intelligence in the assigned business area.● Collaborate with key stakeholders to understand gaps and areas of opportunity to establish models, data sets,marts, and the related reports, dashboards, and/or models.● Partner with departmental owners of business analytics and/or data to drive data and business intelligenceprovisioning towards a self-service model of consumption.● Build strong relationships with business leaders across the organization to understand overall reporting needs andlearn different lines of business. Assess departmental needs and consult on business intelligence data.● Partner with data architecture team and ensure that all data reporting aligns with established data architectureprocesses and standards.● Document, model and communicate data structures to the architecture team and other data resources.● Serve as subject matter expert for departmental reporting and dashboard creation.● Understand all departmental data contained within any data marts and source systems. Leverage data forreporting purposes and create new data marts, sets or cubes when necessary.● Regularly compile data, analyze data sets and visualize data to produce concise and actionable analytical reportsfor business leaders and stakeholders.● Perform ad-hoc analysis to find solutions for business inquiries.● Teach business leaders how to pull, analyze and interpret data. Instruct how to create dashboards to enable longterm self-service capabilities.● Lead efforts to resolve escalated issues by partnering and managing relationships with internal stakeholders andexternal agencies.● Analyze existing SQL server processes to identify gaps, opportunities and strengths. Identify and recommendsolutions for business intelligence capabilities to enhance FirstKey Homes data systems.● Establish processes to audit business intelligence solutions to ensure data integrity. Identify and introduce newindustry standards and techniques to enhance data integrity.● Train, develop and manage a team of business intelligence team members to achieve organizational goals. Coachand mentor direct reports to enhance skillsets and departmental capabilities.● This brief summary is not an all-inclusive description of job duties. Other job duties and responsibilities may alsobe assigned by the incumbent’s manager at any time based upon Company need.  
  
REQUIRED EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE● Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or equivalent work experience and/or education● Minimum 3 years’ experience leading a team of developers to achieve organizational goals.● Minimum 8 years’ experience supporting business intelligence initiatives● Minimum 10 years’ experience working in an information technology role● High proficiency with Microsoft Business Intelligence Stack (SQL Server, SSIS, SSAS, SSRS, PowerBI)● Experience with developing and maintaining data warehouses from multiple systems.● Demonstrated ability to document, maintain and reinforce departmental processes.● Proven ability to interface with business leaders to strategize and execute business intelligence solutionsPREFERRED EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE● Experience using SQL and related services in the Azure cloud a plus● Experience mentoring and coaching team members● Experience working in property management, real estate or similar industry● Experience working in a fast pace, high-growth company

*Must have Fundraising experience*  
  
   
Position Summary   
  
This position is part of the Information Technology (IT) team which provides information technology solutions that enable direct data-driven decision making by the Development Organization. You will be responsible for management and development of business intelligence and analytics solutions, including internal workflows for the Development Organization. This is a new position reports directly to the Senior Director of Enterprise Applications and Administrative Support.  
   
Responsibilities   
   
·         Partner with Alumni Affairs and Development:  
o    Create and manage financial, statistical, forecast and ad-hoc reports and data models on a regular basis  
o    Deliver timely and targeted information, robust tools and insights to help the department become a more data-driven organization  
o    Rapid analysis of Development Organization data challenges to help build solutions that can be leveraged across the Development team  
o    Use advanced statistical concepts to determine significant sources of process or business function variability; determine recommendations for efficiencies  
o    Coordinate between departments and develop cross-departmental reports  
   
·         Designing and implementing data integration from multiple systems resulting in advanced analytic capabilities:  
o    Writing relational and multidimensional database SQL queries  
o    Developing automated tools and dashboards using Business Objects, Tableau or other development tools to provide actionable information to decision makers.  
o    Develop data marts to enable user empowerment via tools such as Business Objects, Crystal Reports or Tableau.  
o    Provide institutional data research and analytics  
   
·         Investigate and troubleshoot data workflow issues for departments on our enterprise systems (Colleague/Slate/Advance)  
·         Provide end-user support for CRM and reporting software  
o    Develop, manage and maintain workflows in CRM platforms  
·         Create best practice documentation and procedures  
·         Provide technical support during upcoming migrations  
·         Projects as assigned  
   
Qualifications  
   
·         3-5 years of experience in business analytics, consulting, data science, business intelligence, data quality and/or data engineering  
·         Fundraising experience  
·         This role requires someone who can shift focus quickly and keep projects within scope. The successful candidate will be comfortable working in a dynamic, data-driven environment and demonstrate a natural curiosity when digging into the numbers.  
·         Ability to work with all levels of the organization up-to and including Executive Leaders.  
·         Degree in business, statistics, database management or related field preferred  
·         Crystal reports, Tableau, Advanced Power BI, Microsoft SQL Reporting Services (SSRS) and data warehousing skills preferred  
·         Advanced Excel and Querying skills; substantial experience with data analysis and modeling, process improvement  
·         Ability to identify trends and clearly distill and present complex data to colleagues who may not have a technical background  
·         Strong analytical and technical expertise in developing business intelligence solutions/tools/reports.  
·         Excellent conceptual, analytical and quantitative skills.  
·         Ability to translate business needs into reporting solutions.  
·         Sense of urgency to drive impact.  
·         Ability to quickly establish subject matter expertise in a variety of business applications.  
·         Excellent verbal, analytical and problem-solving skills  
·         Critical, creative thinker, with the ability to provide data-driven insights and recommendations and see ideas through to completion  
·         Excellent communication skills both orally and verbally.  
·         Unflappable and steady personality who can stay calm under pressure.  
·         Personable and easily builds business relationships/partnerships.  
·         Excellent organizational and prioritization skills  
·         Ability to set goals, establish timelines, and ensure that key milestones and deliverables are met  
·         Ability to quickly relate data to processes within disparate departments such as Alumni Affairs, Fund Raising, Finance and Admissions    
·         Prior experience with fundraising databases and in particular CRM: Advance or Blackbaud CRM, a plus

Nexstar DigitalGreater Los Angeles Area 
About Us  
Nexstar's digital media products and services focus on providing innovative solutions to audiences, clients and any business looking to gain an edge in the shifting digital landscape. Along with Nexstar's dedication to providing local news, entertainment, and sports content through its digital platforms, Nexstar Digital's companies provide digital publishing and content management platforms, a video advertising platform, digital agency services and other digital media solutions to publishers and advertisers.  
Position Description  
The Vice President of Business Intelligence (the “VP”) will be a senior member of the management team responsible for creating customer and business value from the Company’s unique data assets. Reporting to the Senior Vice President of Nexstar Digital, the VP will work closely with other senior stakeholders including Product, Revenue and Operations, Content, Engineering, and Business Development. The ideal candidate will be a highly motivated, passionate leader from a data-driven environment that operates equally as effectively in both independent and team collaboration settings. He/she should have strong business acumen, solid technology experience, and familiarity with the broadcast industry in addition to possessing excellent data science skills.  
  
The VP will be responsible for the creation and execution of an innovative, enterprise-wide BI vision and strategy to establish the capabilities necessary to generate meaningful, actionable insights into user, subscriber and advertiser behavior across our entire network. He/She will be responsible for collecting, managing, and analyzing consumer, product, social, market, competitive, and ad data to lead high impact projects that move our business into the future. It is also a unique opportunity to build a new team and a new set of capabilities for a large broadcast company.

Overview 
  
Highgate’s Business Intelligence team is responsible for managing the majority of Highgate’s standardized operational reporting and situational analysis for the managed hotel portfolio as well as various business support and partnership initiatives to create value within the hotels and the management company. The team is comprised of cross-functional subject matter specialists who work together and in collaboration with other Highgate operating disciplines to achieve these goals and objectives.  
Highgate Hotels is seeking a Director of Business Intelligence to join our team and be a leader in driving the vision and continued development of Highgate’s best-in-class advanced data & analytics platform. This individual will perform analysis using large data sets to help the business understand current performance and identify areas for improvement. This individual will design interactive data visualization reporting that allows business users to explore actionable insights in support of the hotel portfolio’s performance and the Company’s growth strategy, including overseeing an end-to-end user experience from acceptance testing to ongoing training and support to ensure dashboards continue to be relevant and consumed. This role requires an individual who can build positive relationships throughout the organization while becoming intimately familiar with Highgate’s common business language to identify and rationalize opportunities for reporting design, answer key business questions and ensure user adoption. This individual should be ready and willing to actively ascertain opportunities to improve the Company’s data workflow processes and propose alternatives to improve the stability, performance and accuracy of Highgate’s reporting infrastructure.  
   
This role will interface with all Highgate business departments, system vendors, ownership group analyst teams, senior leadership and other external third parties. This role is a great opportunity to utilize an existing technical skillset within a vertically integrated and entrepreneurial platform to be a part of Highgate’s continued expansion and success.

Senior Analyst, Sales and Marketing 
  
As the leading custom payable solution for the Real Estate industry, Nexus is a high-growth software company continuing our expansion. We are looking for an experienced senior financial professional to be part of an aggressive and dynamic sales team focused exclusively on Commercial and Multi-Family Real Estate companies. You will be an active part of the team that represents one of the most widely accepted, productive, and reliable Procure to Pay solutions available. We are seeking a Senior Analyst to coordinate, roll-up, and balance initiatives across Nexus’s sales and marketing opportunities and provide leadership with data-driven decision support. Reporting to the Chief Revenue Officer, our ideal Senior Analyst is someone who wants to work with Sales and Marketing to provide a wide range of financial and decision support to top management, including forecasts, sales result analysis, evaluation/coordination/modeling of new initiatives, and other ad hoc projects. The Senior Analyst will have significant exposure to Senior Management and must become a trusted thought partner across the company.   
  
Responsibilities:  
·       Collaborate with internal finance team and functional partners to lead strategic analyses to address the evolving business, identifying areas of risk and opportunity, and collaborating on strategies to achieve revenue targets 
·       Drive ongoing sales forecasts in close coordination with corporate finance team. Prepare monthly and quarterly variances analysis of revenue.  
·       Execute and evolve our planning process. Create and manage operational reports and dashboards to monitor revenue performance. Develop tools to track and report various aspects of the business.  
·       Develop solutions to optimize sales close rates and optimize ongoing sales and marketing performance 
·       Collaborate with key stakeholders to understand the story behind numbers and synthesize results in a concise manner, while highlighting key trends. Be able to facilitate senior management and board reporting.  
·       Develop financial business case and analysis for new pricing and product initiatives 
·       Special Projects: For example: implement best practices in planning process and software tools, including internal file and client activity monitoring. 
  
Qualifications: 
·       3+ years of financial analysis experience in a technology company.  
·       Bachelor’s Degree in Finance or Accounting, or related discipline. 
·       Analytical background working directly in a strategic finance or business operations environment modeling ROI cases, bookings, revenue, expenses, etc. 
·       Advanced Microsoft Excel modeling skills, with competency in Word, PowerPoint and deep experience in Salesforce CRM. 
·       Diligent, highly accurate with attention to detail, exceptional organizational skills, and the ability to demonstrate excellent time-management. 
·       Demonstrated thought-leadership, teamwork. Able to anticipate business needs and manage relationships with key stakeholders. 
·       Demonstration of critical thinking—ability to question the output of a financial model or investment case and consider options for improvement or provide thoughtful alternatives. 
·       Proactive, results oriented, with a can-do attitude.

Publicis Health Media (PHM) is the strategic media planning and  buying agency within PHCG, and the only global media agency solely  dedicated to the health and wellness space. PHM’s core is made up of franchise and enterprise AOR relationships  with some of the largest clients in the world. We also partner with PHCG  and Groupe creative agencies to support large client brand assignments  in health and wellness. FlexIT GlobalPortland, Oregon Area 
As an Expert Threat Intelligence Analyst your role in the Threat Intelligence team is to assist the  Corporate Information Security team by researching and analyzing current and emerging threats and vulnerabilities that have the potential to cause harm or malicious actions against the environment. You will maintain awareness of the cyber threat landscape and leverage automation to build better detection capabilities.  This role will also provide direct support to the Cyber Defense Center (CDC), Incident Response, and CIS Ops management team.  
   
 If you believe in a business risk balanced approach and you excel in a highly-matrixed, people-focused environment this is the place for you. If you believe that sport can change the world, this is the place for you.  
   
Qualifications  
  
 · You have intimate knowledge about information security threat intelligence and thrive on the details of threat analysis. You know what's possible and what's not. You know how to determine what's relevant. · You are a strong people leader. You know how to build and motivate teams and individuals and help them grow to their potential. · Your ethics and ability to manage sensitive material are unquestionable. · Change is an opportunity and ambiguity doesn't rattle you. · Work life balance is as important to you as it is to us. However, the occasional ad-hoc change of evening or weekend plans you see as a collective opportunity to excel.  
 But also:  
 · Your formal education and experience is, or is similar to, a bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Information Security/Assurance, Engineering, or related field of study.  
· You have experience in and understand the full stack of cyber threat modelling to identify potential threats.  
· You have excellent written and verbal communication skills required. You are able to communicate details in a clear, business relevant manner. · You have a Customer-oriented focus, with a strong interest in a satisfied client. · And, you take pride in being diligent and self-driven.

full_desc:
DSD LabsPearl Harbor, Hawaii 
DSD Laboratories, Inc. is looking for talented individuals that have recent experience in IT and software development/configuration to work on cutting edge technologies and capabilities that bring data/information together to support leadership decision making, wartime planning and business/mission execution, commonly known as a logistics common operating picture. Your skills and expertise will help us identify user requirements, collaborate with developers, acquire and integrate the required data/information, and deliver a variety of visualization capabilities to the users and stakeholders. 
 
Candidate will support HQ Pacific Air Forces (PACAF) Air Force Forces (AFFOR) Logistics Common Operating Picture (LOGCOP), an information management and visualization capability.  
 
Candidate will: 
- Capture and manage user and mission requirements 
- Conduct user interviews at all organizational levels to identify, analyze, and document user requirements.  
- Perform engineering design evaluations and create requirements traceability matrices to ensure that design fully supports functional requirements.  
- Make design and solution recommendations – identifying options and creating prototypes to exploit enterprise services, leveraging business intelligence tools like Tableau, SAP Business Objects, and IBM Cognos.  
- Collaborate with program management and development team to ensure requirements are met, to maximize reuse of existing capabilities and data 
- Lead or participate in system development lifecycle milestone reviews (requirements, design, test, and deployment). 
- Collaborate with the appropriate resources to identify authoritative data sources to support requirements and propose technical solutions and options to make information available to support operational needs.  
- Modify / create repeatable processes and reusable templates to manage the lifecycle of the LOGCOP (requirements specification, traceability matrix, wireframes, prototypes, etc.). 
- Develop training materials for various levels of the organization 
- Collaborate with users to troubleshoot functionality issues.  
- Update senior leadership and make recommendations for strategic planning and prioritization of requirements, technologies, and data acquisition to meet customer goals.  
 
Experience:  
 
Estimated travel is less than 5%.
